data.name: ALZO International Inc.
data.description: ALZO International works to proactively address the increasingly urgent need for commodity ingredients which are produced without causing harm to the environment or society. Our esters, cationic conditioners, emollients, silicone elastomers provide an excellent alternative to petroleum-based ingredients, while our natural surfactant in a liquid form provides long-lasting foam and antimicrobial activity and is readily biodegradable. Importantly, ALZO is certified by the Roundtable of Sustainable Palm Oil Supply Chain Certification Standard (RSPO SCCS).

data.name: Dermol™ SLLC-L
data.description: Dermol SLLC-L is a unique liquid surfactant derived from sodium isostearoyl lactylate. It functions as an emulsifier and cleanser with excellent conditioning properties for hair and skin and adds moisturizing, anti-static and viscosity boosting benefits.

data.name: BioMade HS-DD
data.description:
BioMade HS-DD i s an excellent film forming polymeric emollient ester with numerous cosmetic applications. Naturally derived from refined hemp seed oil, it helps
to retain water in creams and lotions as well as adding body and spreading properties in emulsions. It provides outstanding shine, water retention and adhesion, and is an excellent pigment wetter for color cosmetics. BioMade HS-DD is a natural alternative to petroleum-based & synthetic film formers. BioMade HS-DD has also shown to significantly improve SPF water resistance in sun care formulations.

data.name: Beantree®
data.description: Beantree® is a totally natural clear liquid derived from castor & rapeseed, which has low viscosity. It has a light, dry feel that is non-oily and which absorbs quickly into the skin. This product is oil and alcohol soluble, has low odor, reduces tack and greasiness, has solvent properties, has a high gloss/sheen and is suitable for use in skin care, color cosmetics, hair care, and bath products.

data.name: Bernel Ester™ TCC
data.description: Bernel Ester TCC is a natural ester derived from tricaprylyl citrate.  It is suitable for use in waterproof formulations and as an alternative for jojoba oil and squalane.

data.description: Dermol SCLL-L is a unique liquid surfactant derived from sodium lauroyl lactylate. It functions as an emulsifier and cleanser with excellent conditioning properties for hair and skin and adds moisturizing, anti-static and viscosity boosting benefits.

data.name: Polyderm™ PPI-CO-40
data.description: Polyderm™ PPI-CO-40 is a vegetable derived water soluble polyurethane where the triol is an ethoxylated-hydrogenated castor oil. Polyderm™ PPI-CO-40 exhibits substantivity due to the presence of urethane bond (carbamate bond). It also offers conditioning, lubricity and slip to both skin and hair products. Polyderm™ PPI-CO-40 can be used as an emulsifying agent, a coupling agent and as a surfactant in cosmetic formulations where it leaves a silky feel.

data.name: Dermol™ M-5
data.description: Dermol M-5 is a naturally derived ester that is a cost effective co-solvent and coupler.  It is non-oily and penetrating with low irritation.

data.name: Hetester
data.seo_description: View all ALZO International Inc. Hetester products on Knowde.com. Quickly and easily request a quote, get samples, and download data sheets.

data.name: Hetester™ PMA
data.description: Hetester PMA is an excellent solvent and plasticizer for use in anhydrous oil systems, especially when waxes are present, as well as an all-purpose, cost efficient emollient with an elegantly light, dry feel for various types of emulsions.

data.name: Hetester™ PHA
data.description: Hetester PHA is a water-soluble, clear, white to pale yellow-colored liquid. This product is most commonly used as an anti-chalking agent in anhydrous volatile silicone roll-on antiperspirant formulation applications. Due to its "blooming" property, Hetester PHA can also be used as a pigment wetter in foundation lotion and pigment cosmetic applications.

data.name: Hetester™ PCA
data.description: Hetester PCA is a water-soluble, clear white to pale yellow-colored liquid. This product is most commonly used as an anti-chalking agent in anhydrous volatile silicone oil roll-on antiperspirant formulation applications. Hetester PCA can also be used as a pigment wetter in foundation lotion applications.

data.name: Hetester™ FAO
data.description: Hetester FAO is a branched chain ester that is a suitable alternative to IPM, an electrolyte stabilizer and hardness reducer in stick products.

data.name: Hetester™ HCA
data.description: Hetester HCA is a hazy yellow, viscous liquid derived from castor oil and glycerin. It is a lubricious ester with substance and film forming properties that add high gloss to lipsticks, body to mascaras, and long-lasting wear to foundations.

data.name: Hetester™ SSS
data.description: Hetester SSS is a solid, waxy emollient that when combined 50/50 with certain oils, forms an amorphous solid mass whose melting point can be raised substantially with as little as 5% of Ozokerite Wax or equivalent wax. Therefore, this ester can be a major component of a myriad of cosmetic stick formulations. In emulsion systems where a solid emollient is required, Hetester SSS offers its own distinctive emolliency with the additional benefit of relative ease of emulsification.

data.name: Hetester™ 412
data.description: Hetester™ 412 is a solid ester used effectively as an emollient, opacifier and thickener for creams, lotions and lipsticks. It is also used as a conditioner and sheen additive for skin preparations and as a base material in solid cosmetic products.

data.name: Hetester™ HSS
data.description: Hetester HSS is a clear yellow liquid with a mild, typical odor. It disperses high levels of pigments, provides cushion and a soft after feel in emulsions and liquid makeup.
